findings.recommended_fix:
Develop a clear procedure and explicit reference to the list of line maintenance locations, for example:
"X.X Line Maintenance Locations
(a) The organisation performs line maintenance only at locations identified and listed in Appendix YY 'Line Maintenance Locations'. This includes permanent and temporary line maintenance points.
(b) Temporary line maintenance points may be established to support occasional line maintenance or AOG situations. Prior to use, the Maintenance Manager (or delegate) ensures that:
  • suitable facilities and environmental conditions are available;
  • required tools, equipment and calibrated test devices are available;
  • applicable maintenance data is available and current;
  • appropriately authorised certifying staff are present.
(c) Each temporary line maintenance point is recorded in the 'Catalogue of Temporary Line Maintenance Points' (Appendix YY), including location, validity period, scope of work and responsible manager.
(d) The MOE and its appendices are kept up to date so that all active line maintenance locations are listed, in accordance with 145.A.75(d)."
